--- before RC tarball
    * make sure schema.sql is up to date
    * Change the release number in /init.php (APP_VERSION)
    * Update the ChangeLog file with the correct version number and release date
	* Update UPGRADE with instructions, check misc/upgrade new files have proper text and versions
	* Localization: make pot, review, commit
	$ make -C misc/localization pot
	$ make -C misc/localization update-po

--- making RC tarball
    * Set proper rc=RC1 in release.sh
    $ ./release.sh

--- after RC
	* Use last RC tarball you like for release. if any svn commits after RC remake tarball.
    * Tag the repository with the new release (svn copy trunk/eventum/ tags/eventum-2.0)
	$ svn cp svn://eventum.mysql.org/eventum-gpl/trunk/eventum svn://eventum.mysql.org/eventum-gpl/tags/eventum-2.1

--- after release
   * update freshmeat: http://freshmeat.net/projects/eventum/




---------------------
    * make sure schema.sql is up to date
    * Change the release number in /init.php (APP_VERSION)
    * Update the ChangeLog file with the correct version number and release date
	* Update UPGRADE with instructions, check misc/upgrade new files have proper text and versions
    * Commit those changes
    * Tag the repository with the new release (svn copy trunk/eventum/ tags/eventum-2.0)

	$ svn cp svn://eventum.mysql.org/eventum-gpl/trunk/eventum svn://eventum.mysql.org/eventum-gpl/tags/eventum-2.1

    * Commit changes (svn commit)
    * Export the release tag into a separate directory (cd tags/eventum-2.0/; svn export . ../../../releases/eventum-2.0) 

    * Make the following directories writeable (chmod -R 777 $dir_name):
          o templates_c
          o locks
          o logs
          o config 

chmod -R 777 templates_c
chmod -R 777 locks
chmod -R 777 logs
chmod -R 777 config

